              <h3>Oven-Baked Salmon with Lemon and Dill:</h3>
              <p>
                Description: A healthy and flavorful salmon dish with a zesty lemon and dill seasoning.
                Ingredients: Salmon fillets, lemon, fresh dill, olive oil, salt, pepper.
                Instructions:
                Preheat the oven to 400°F (300°C).
                Place the salmon fillets on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
                Drizzle olive oil over the salmon and season with salt and pepper.
                Squeeze fresh lemon juice over the fillets and sprinkle chopped dill on top.
                Bake in the preheated oven for <strong>13-15</strong> minutes or until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.
                Serve hot and garnish with additional lemon slices and dill sprigs.
              </p>
