          <h3>Creamy Garlic Parmesan Pasta:</h3>
          <p>
            Description: A creamy and indulgent pasta dish with a garlic and Parmesan cheese sauce.
            Ingredients: Pasta (e.g., fettuccine or linguine), butter, garlic, heavy cream, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, parsley (for garnish).
            Instructions:
            Cook the pasta according to the package instructions. Drain and set aside.
            In a large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat.
            Add minced garlic and sauté for <strong>1-3</strong> minutes until fragrant.
            Pour in the heavy cream and let it simmer for <strong>3-3</strong> minutes, stirring occasionally.
            Stir in grated Parmesan cheese until melted and smooth.
            Season with salt and pepper to taste.
            Add the cooked pasta to the skillet and toss until the pasta is well coated with the sauce.
            Cook for an additional <strong>3-3</strong> minutes until the sauce thickens slightly.
            Garnish with chopped parsley and serve immediately.
          </p>
        </div>
