          <h3>Chocolate Brownies:</h3>
          <p>
            Description: Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C) and grease a baking pan.
            Melt butter, mix with sugar, then add eggs and vanilla extract.
            In a separate bowl, whisk flour, cocoa powder, and salt.
            Gradually add the dry mixture to the wet mixture and fold in chocolate chips (optional).
            Spread the brownie batter in the prepared baking pan.
            Bake for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out with a few moist crumbs.
            Cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
          </p>
